{"TopicId":213146,"ForumId":196,"TopicTitle":"Map View Camera Speed depends on Latitude","CreatedByName":"Pkmniako","CreatedById":138569,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T12:31:37Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Pkmniako","CreatedById":138569,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T12:31:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis small oversight should be very easy to fix.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn mapview, the camera\u0027s speed when it rotates around a planet depends on Latitude. This means when the camera is closer to the poles of the planet, the horizontal speed of the camera drops drastically.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdditional Information about the computer used:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCPU: Ryzen 9 5900X\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGPU: GTX 970\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRAM: 32GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-02-26T12:33:46Z\u0022 title=\u002202/26/2023 12:33  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 26, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Pkmniako\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LezRowl","CreatedById":213344,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T16:38:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am getting this issue too, however not as described.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I am experiencing is that the speed of the camera decreases the further\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eup/north\u00A0\u003C/em\u003Eyou go, relative to whatever you are focused on.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt also seems that when focused on the kerbal, the camera only goes up to a certain angle and no further. This renders you unable to freely look at the top of Kerbin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EWhen focused on Kerbin (see attachment)\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/kwvxM99YJ1U?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Bug Map View Camera Speed Kerbin\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EWhen focused on a Kerbal on the South Pole (see attachment)\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/NokIDVXg6LI?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Bug Map View Camera Speed Kerbal SouthPole\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pkmniako","CreatedById":138569,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T19:20:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224244400\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022213146\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677429499\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022213344\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022LezRowl\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, LezRowl said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am getting this issue too, however not as described.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I am experiencing is that the speed of the camera decreases the further\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eup/north\u00A0\u003C/em\u003Eyou go, relative to whatever you are focused on.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt also seems that when focused on the kerbal, the camera only goes up to a certain angle and no further. This renders you unable to freely look at the top of Kerbin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EWhen focused on Kerbin (see attachment)\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/kwvxM99YJ1U?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Bug Map View Camera Speed Kerbin\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EWhen focused on a Kerbal on the South Pole (see attachment)\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/NokIDVXg6LI?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Bug Map View Camera Speed Kerbal SouthPole\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBeen able to test this again. Your description matches the behaviour seen better.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}